title: Lunch
text:
Had a lovely lunch woodland salad was delicious.
with friendly service
My sister had the duck sandwich.

title: Stetson mansion
text:
Wow what a wonderful job on renovations !
The tour was wonderful Cindy and JoAnn, . These ladies are awesome and full of energy and entertaining with a wealth of information about family and the mansion .
JT and Michael your vision and decorating of the mansion was outstanding .
Looking forward to another project you both might be doing in future to add to my tours .
Thanks for a great outing I enjoyed this with tour my sister .

title: Nan Lian Gardens
text: Great spot in the city yet you want to get out of the hustle bustle of the big city . Nice quiet and tranquil .

title: Excellent food and staff
text:
Had a great Steak with mushroom sauce .
Staff was amazing as was the company I was with .
I would definitely go back .its a small place but I do recommend it .

title: Cocktail hour !
text: Very nice place for cocktails before dinner or after . Great view of Acropolis lite up at night ! Definite Photo opp .

title: Wow
text:
It’s been years since I’ve been to Acropolis but they are doing a great job on restoring it .
You can make a full day of walking around the area .

title: High tea!
text:
Had hight tea and champagne with my sister !
This is our favorite store to visit anytime we’re in London!
Love the architect of the building inside and out :

title: My favorite coffee
text: This is by far my favorite coffee choice in London or any country that has one . I will always chose this over other coffee places

title: Lunch at the crypt
text:
Enjoy going to the Crypt for lunch on my visits to London .
Food is good enjoy the surroundings . I recommend this to friends
And family .

title: Wonderful service and food
text:
Wow had a great meal and wonderful service !
Highly recommend
Wait staff was amazing ! I would definitely go back again .

title: Dinner
text:
We had a group of 7 and everyone had a delicious meal !
I would recommend this play great steaks !
Looking forward to going again on next visit .

title: Cape Canaveral cruise parking
text:
Go Port Canaveral parking was painless and I would highly recommend .
You can book ahead online which made our vacation stress free .

title: Girls night out
text: Loved the Place and the food was wonderful,! I highly recommend for food or just drinks great atmosphere .

title: Titanic
text:
Great day spent at the museum ,enjoyed learning more details about the making of the ship and its fateful sailing . .
Also visited the Nomadic and learned about its history having no previous knowledge of this ship .
A must see if your visiting Belfast .

title: Hilton
text:
Comfortable hotel with a Costa coffee shop on property . The staff are very helpful with arranging tours .
The tour I book even picked up and dropped off at hotel . Also about a 20 min walk to to Tiranic Museum .

title: Giant causeway tour
text:
Great tour of the Giant Causway with Derek the tour guide / driver . I would highly recommend this tour company and Derek.
I enjoyed my lunch at Bushmills distillery and the beautiful coastal drive .
All in all it was a fun and informative day . Thanks Derek for your professionalism
And bad jokes lol.

title: Cliffs of Moher day tour !
text:
The Burren and the Cliffs of Moher tour given by Frank was outstanding . Frank is very knowledgeable about the history and has a wonderful sense of humor . Frank made for wonderful day outing I would highly recommend the Barratt tours and especially Frank .

My crew had a great time !
Thanks Frank and Barratt tours !
Sept 09, 2015
place: Full-Day Small-Group Cliffs Of Moher Day Trip from Limerick

title: King John castle
text: Enjoyed my visit very informative and interactive . Great for kids to learn the history . Friendly staff very nice gift shop and cafe .

title: Church
text: Beautiful church and grounds . Entrance fee of £4 euro but work it to help maintain the historical features of the church .
